[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man rescued from flat fire at Bridgend

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man had to be rescued from a first-floor flat fire, said South Wales Fire and Rescue Service.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
He was treated at the scene for smoke inhalation following the incident at Bryntirion, Bridgend.
Two fire engines responded to the callout after 01:30 BST on Saturday.
The fire was caused by unattended cooking, said the fire service.
